# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: PrisonArc | Scene: OutsideAndAlone
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "There is no place for me here, I'm sorry. Please, allow me to leave."
    new "There is no place for me here, I'm sorry. Please, allow me to leave."

    old "Vaelen looks at Sarah. She sees an odd mixture of surprise and sadness in his eyes."
    new "Vaelen looks at Sarah. She sees an odd mixture of surprise and sadness in his eyes."

    old "Very well, Sarah. You have made your choice, and I will not keep you here against your will."
    new "Very well, Sarah. You have made your choice, and I will not keep you here against your will."

    old "I will instruct the guards to let you pass, and you are free to go. However, you are not free to stay here."
    new "I will instruct the guards to let you pass, and you are free to go. However, you are not free to stay here."

    old "Sarah bows her head."
    new "Sarah bows her head."

    old "I understand, farewell, commander Vaelen."
    new "I understand, farewell, commander Vaelen."

    old "Sarah turns around and exits the tent."
    new "Sarah turns around and exits the tent."

    old "Not long after she exits, she hears Kate run up behind her."
    new "Not long after she exits, she hears Kate run up behind her."

    old "Sarah, wait!"
    new "Sarah, wait!"

    old "Sarah turns around to face her old friend."
    new "Sarah turns around to face her old friend."

    old "Why did you turn him down?"
    new "Why did you turn him down?"

    old "What did you think I was going to do? Sign up and become a soldier? I've never even punched a person in my life, let alone swung a sword."
    new "What did you think I was going to do? Sign up and become a soldier? I've never even punched a person in my life, let alone swung a sword."

    old "If you put me out on a battlefield, I'd be dead in under an hour."
    new "If you put me out on a battlefield, I'd be dead in under an hour."

    old "But...I could have helped you, trained you..."
    new "But...I could have helped you, trained you..."

    old "Kate, I never wanted to be here in the first place."
    new "Kate, I never wanted to be here in the first place."

    old "You whisked me away to the other side of the world on a lie, and now my home is gone. I have nothing left."
    new "You whisked me away to the other side of the world on a lie, and now my home is gone. I have nothing left."

    old "When I think about Thomas and how he was alone when he..."
    new "When I think about Thomas and how he was alone when he..."

    old "Sarah couldn't bring herself to finish her sentence."
    new "Sarah couldn't bring herself to finish her sentence."

    old "You did that."
    new "You did that."

    old "I never forced you to take my hand."
    new "I never forced you to take my hand."

    old "Sarah felt her anger growing."
    new "Sarah felt her anger growing."

    old "Fine, then don't even feel responsible for what you did. I don't need to to feel anything, I'm done with this place, and I'm done with you."
    new "Fine, then don't even feel responsible for what you did. I don't need to to feel anything, I'm done with this place, and I'm done with you."

    old "Sarah tried to turn around to walk away, but felt Kate grab onto her shoulder, pulling her back to face her."
    new "Sarah tried to turn around to walk away, but felt Kate grab onto her shoulder, pulling her back to face her."

    old "Sarah, you don't know what you're doing."
    new "Sarah, you don't know what you're doing."

    old "This city, this world, it's a dangerous place. You go out there alone, with nothing and nobody, they'll eat you alive."
    new "This city, this world, it's a dangerous place. You go out there alone, with nothing and nobody, they'll eat you alive."

    old "I'm not as foolish as you imagine me, and I know this world is full of snakes, I'm looking at one right now."
    new "I'm not as foolish as you imagine me, and I know this world is full of snakes, I'm looking at one right now."

    old "Then, for the first time in her life, Sarah did strike someone."
    new "Then, for the first time in her life, Sarah did strike someone."

    old "Kate seemed unable to process the slap across her face, staring, stunned at Sarah as she walked away."
    new "Kate seemed unable to process the slap across her face, staring, stunned at Sarah as she walked away."

    old "Something had broken between them, and it would not be fixed."
    new "Something had broken between them, and it would not be fixed."

